\begin_inset Formula $\tau<\infty$
\end_inset 

, and if furthermore its growth is bounded on the imaginary axis, so that
 
\begin_inset Formula \[
f(iy)=\mathcal{O}(1)e^{-c|y|}\]

\end_inset 

for 
\begin_inset Formula $c<\pi$
\end_inset 

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset 

 is identically zero.
 
