The integrand of the corresponding Norlund-Rice integral is regular at 
\begin_inset Formula $s=1$
\end_inset 

 and has a simple pole at 
\begin_inset Formula $s=0$
\end_inset 

, and a double pole at 
\begin_inset Formula $s=2$
\end_inset 

.
 In most other respects, it resembles the integral for the Mobius series.
 The residue of the pol at 
\begin_inset Formula $s=0$
\end_inset 

 contributes 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\mbox{Res}\left(s=0\right)=-\frac{\zeta(-1)}{\zeta(0)}=-\frac{1}{6}\]

\end_inset 

 while that at 
\begin_inset Formula $s=2$
\end_inset 

 contributes 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray*}
\mbox{Res}\left(s=2\right) & = & \Gamma\left(n+1\right)\left.\frac{d}{ds}\left[\frac{(s-2)^{2}\zeta(s-1)\Gamma(-s)}{\zeta(s)\Gamma(n-s+1)}\right]\right|_{s=2}\\
 & = & \frac{3n(n-1)}{\pi^{2}}\left[\frac{3}{2}-\gamma+\log\left(2\pi\right)-12\log A-\psi(n-1)\right]\\
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset 

 Here, the constant 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset 

 is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant 
\begin_inset Formula $A=1.28242712910062263687534256886979\ldots$
\end_inset 

.
 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi(n)$
\end_inset 

 is the digamma function, which is just the harmonic number at the integers:
 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\psi(n)=-\gamma+\sum_{k=1}^{n-1}\frac{1}{k}\]

\end_inset 

As before, the residues of the trivial zeros contribute 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{O}(1/n^{2})$
\end_inset 

 to the sum.
 These are 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\mbox{Res}\left(s<0\right)=\frac{n!}{2\pi^{2}}\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}\frac{(2k+1)!}{(2k+n)!}\;\frac{\zeta(2k+2)}{k\zeta(2k+1)}\]

\end_inset 

Thus, the analytic development indicates that 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
d_{n}^{\varphi}=\mbox{Res}\left(s\le2\right)-\sum_{\rho}\frac{\Gamma(n+1)\Gamma(-\rho)}{\Gamma(n-\rho+1)}\,\frac{\zeta(\rho-1)}{\zeta^{\prime}(\rho)}\label{eq:}\end{equation}

\end_inset 

 for the series.
 
\layout Standard

It seems that, at least for the small zeroes, one has that 
\begin_inset Formula $\zeta(\rho-1)\sim1$
\end_inset 

, and so, just as in the Mobius function sums, one has oscillatory behavior
 given by
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
d_{n}^{\varphi}-\mbox{Res}\left(s\le2\right)=2\sqrt{n+1}\sum_{n\gg\tau>0}\Re\left[\Gamma\left(-\frac{1}{2}-i\tau\right)e^{i\tau\log(n+1)}\frac{\zeta\left(-\frac{1}{2}+i\tau\right)}{\zeta^{\prime}\left(\frac{1}{2}+i\tau\right)}\right]\label{eq:}\end{equation}

